VITE_DATA_SOURCE=

# Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD) App Registration - required for real
# "Sign in with Microsoft" login and for sending partner report emails via
# Microsoft Graph (see src/services/msalAuth.ts and graphMailService.ts).
# Leave these blank to keep using the demo email/password login untouched.
#
# Setup steps (Azure Portal > Entra ID > App registrations > New registration):
#   1. Name it anything (e.g. "Supplier Management System").
#   2. Supported account types: "Accounts in this organizational directory only".
#   3. Redirect URI: platform "Single-page application (SPA)", value = the
#      exact URL this app is served from (e.g. http://localhost:3000 for dev,
#      and your production URL - add both as separate redirect URIs).
#   4. After creation, copy "Application (client) ID" and "Directory (tenant) ID"
#      from the Overview page into the two variables below.
#   5. API permissions > Add a permission > Microsoft Graph > Delegated:
#      add User.Read and Mail.Send. No admin consent is required for either
#      (both are standard delegated permissions) - each user just consents
#      for themselves on first sign-in.
#   6. No client secret is needed - this is a public client (browser-only,
#      delegated) flow, nothing server-side to secure.
VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID=
# Optional - defaults to window.location.origin if omitted.
VITE_AZURE_REDIRECT_URI=
